  "prompt": "Knock knee cause any problem in Delhi police si selection?",
  "response": "Knock knees, or genu valgum, can potentially affect the selection process for physical fitness tests in certain job roles, including those in law enforcement like the Delhi Police Sub-Inspector (SI) selection. While knock knees are not a disqualifying medical condition on their own, they may impact an individual's performance in physical assessments, which often include running, jumping, and other physical activities.\n\nTypically, medical examinations during the selection process assess a candidate's overall physical health. If knock knees affect physical performance or are associated with other complications, they may be taken into consideration during this evaluation.\n\nIf you have concerns about how knock knees may affect your application or selection, it is advisable to consult with a medical professional who can provide guidance based on your specific situation. It may also help to stay informed about the specific eligibility criteria and medical standards set by the Delhi Police.",
